<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="170" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1580,2037]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1652,1677]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Stonis &amp; Diškus &amp; Remeikis &amp; Solis, 2018" authorityName="Stonis &amp; Diškus &amp; Remeikis &amp; Solis" authorityYear="2018" box="[335,499,1652,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Simplimorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kailai" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Myrtinepticula">
<emphasis box="[335,357,1652,1675]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">S.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[380,411,1653,1676]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[435,499,1652,1676]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">kailai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[513,610,1652,1677]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[513,610,1652,1677]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is distinctive, extremely small and easily recognizable species. The combination of a dark forewing with one silvery white fascia, basally rounded valva, short vinculum with large triangular lateral lobes, and a slender phallus possessing no cornuti in the male genitalia distinguishes 
<taxonomicName authority="Stonis &amp; Diškus &amp; Remeikis &amp; Solis, 2018" authorityName="Stonis &amp; Diškus &amp; Remeikis &amp; Solis" authorityYear="2018" box="[1289,1436,1724,1748]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Simplimorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kailai" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Myrtinepticula">
<emphasis box="[1289,1310,1724,1747]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">S.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1326,1357,1725,1748]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1372,1436,1724,1748]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">kailai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,240,1759,1784]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,240,1759,1784]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
from all 
<taxonomicName box="[344,487,1759,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nepticulidae</taxonomicName>
including the congeneric species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="173" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1580,2037]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1436,151,752]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="173" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1796,1821]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[277,364,1796,1821]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–74" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1896,1918]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,198,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[153,1433,193,1875]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 65–74. Adults of new Simplimorpha (Myrtinepticula) species. 65, S. cercaria Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., male paratype; 66, same, other male paratype; 67, same, abdomen; 68, S. nielseni Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., male paratype, abdomen; 69, same, male holotype; 70, S. kailai Stonis sp. nov, male holotype; 71–74, S. sapphirella Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., female holotype (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2609739/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
). Forewing length about 1.3 mm; wingspan about 3.0 mm. Head: palpi cream; face brownish cream, smooth-scaled, glossy; frontal tuft cream; scape large, glossy cream; antenna half the length of forewing; flagellum with about 17 segments, cream on underside, annulated with dark brown scales on upper side, except for cream base. Thorax and tegula blackish brown. Forewing coarsely speckled with blackish brown scales, with silvery white fascia, and purple iridescence: weak on basal half before fascia, strong on apical part, beyond fascia (therefore the apical area of forewing appears darker); fringe grey, distally cream; underside of forewing dark greybrown, without spots. Hindwing grey to dark grey (depending from angle of view) on upper side and underside, without spots; fringe dark grey. Legs brownish cream with some grey to blackish brown scales on forelegs upper side. Abdomen fuscous on upper side, with numerous cream scales on underside; genital plates large, brownish cream; anal tufts indistinct, brownish cream.
</paragraph>
