<figureCitation box="[459,502,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 122–125" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1935,1957]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,193,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[153,1433,193,1913]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 122–125. Simplimorpha (Myrtinepticula) kailai Stonis, sp. nov. 122, male genitalia, slide AD935, ventral view of capsule; 123, same, dorsal view of capsule; 124, same, phallus; 125, habitat, disturbed tropical premontane forest (south western Amazonian selva), elevation ca. 700 m, Peru, Junín Region, Satipo." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2609761/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">122</figureCitation>
